text: Iqbal Miya is a Nepali politician and a member of the House of Representatives of the federal parliament of Nepal. He was elected from Bara-4 constituency representing Rastriya Janata Party Nepal. He secured 22,275 votes, defeating his nearest rival Dev Narayan Tharu of CPN UML (of the left alliance), who secured 20,608 votes. This is the first time Miya has been elected to parliament. ==References== Category:Living people Category:Members of the House of Representatives (Nepal) Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
